SIMPLE: orgasm
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: orgasm
<hw>or"gasm</hw> <pr>(⟦ocir⟧r"g⟦acr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>orgasme</ets>; cf. Gr. <grk>'orgasmo`s</grk> a kneading, softening,
prob. confused with <grk>'orga^n</grk> to swell, especially with lust;
to feel an ardent desire.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Eager or
immoderate excitement or action; the state of turgescence of any organ;
erethism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Especially:</specif> <def>The peak of the
physical pleasurable sexual excitement caused by stimulation of the
sexual organs, as in intercourse; in the male, it is usually accompanied
by ejaculation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>An eruption of intense,
uncontrolled excitement; -- used of groups and individuals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orgeat</ent>⟦br⟧
